social_posts.post_text: Home sweet home after a few weeks with @mood_change_  and many friends in Mexico & Costa Rica. Managed to surf almost daily with my arm in a brace, learned a lesson in minimalism through 8 days without any luggage, enjoyed many meals with friends from afar, played a super fun show in San Jose ( thx @the_jleon )and caught up on sleep - early to bed and early to rise is so much easier in the tropics. Both countries are rich in culture, beautiful beaches, delicious food, and welcoming people. ❤️ Thx for having us!

Breaking the 📵 rules to ask who wants to win 2 tickets to Friday’s almost sold out show in Nanaimo? Comment below and I’ll pick a winner tomorrow morning at 10am. 

@renegadesoundcollective @jfkillah @just.one.music @the_author_music  @thequeensnanaimo

Much love to everyone who came out! It was a wild ride getting to Nanaimo on Friday with cancelled ferries, a helijet and a stormy drive up island. Rare afterparty moments from Friday. Thx @colinmct for the snaps! Good times.

I’m very excited to share this set with you!  @mood_change_ & I played an all night 6+ hour B2B at @dollydisco on Jan 28th, 2023.  We started before doors opened and were the last ones standing at 6:30am! The recording is now up on SC. Link in bio

We wanted to get lost in the moment, to find that connection with music and the dance floor, and to explore the farther reaches of our libraries. 

We both come from different ends of the genre spectrum but when we play together it’s a sweet spot in the middle.  This set is spontaneous, we played 3 for 3 all night with no plan other than to listen to each other and build on that energy.  The room was dark, packed and sweaty. It sounded great and felt amazing. 

I hope you enjoy this mix and all the imperfections/perfections that come with a wild party - we were enjoying it as much as everyone else.  We had the best time and can’t wait to do it again!

Out tomorrow! Mire rounds out the new Energy Boyz EP on @chapter3records with a driving 4/4 heater. Out on all platforms at midnight June 30th. @garneaumusic & @destrata.dj

12 Fingers EP - Energy Boyz (@garneaumusic & @destrata.dj) is out today on all major platforms. Three distinctly future tracks that were inspired directly by the UK techno sound of the early 2010s. Blending elements of techno, breakbeats and electro, 12 Fingers is a tongue and cheek take on modern day rave music.

CH3 is honoured to host Energy Boyz for the second release on the label. Energy Boyz is the brainchild of Canadian producers Garneau & Destrata. What was initially a DJ project, quickly turned into an outlet for their collaborative originals. While their solo music is relatively different, they were brought together by their mutual love of breakbeats, electro, and low end frequencies. The Energy Boyz project is a tongue in cheek take on modern day rave music. 

Artwork by @samdemoe 
Mastering by @beauteneightsevenmastering

Each of these clips brings me right back to the dance floor.  There was so much good music this past weekend that the biggest challenge was trying to be everywhere at once. At times I bounced between stages trying to catch parts of everyone’s sets, and then other times I surrendered to the moment and stayed in one place letting the sound pick me up and carry me 💗 thank you to everyone who played 💗 @basscoastfest

A couple clips of 12 Fingers by Energy Boyz being played out at @basscoastfest. I am very excited to have just released this track on @chapter3records .  Energy Boyz is @garneaumusic x @destrata.dj  and their tunes have become staples in my sets over the past couple of years. Listen to the full EP through link in bio! I took a few days post @shambhala_mf to go offline and camp.  So here is the first of many photos and moments from an amazing weekend on the farm.  Thank you to @the_living_room_stage for inviting me to play a sunset set on the beach. It was really fun planning music for and playing at that time of day. I started off playing some of the prettier and more melodic tunes in my library and then built the energy to lead us into the evening. And THANK YOU to every one of you who showed up and came along for the ride. I really appreciate all of you on the dance floor so much. That was very special! <3 

To my surprise I ended up playing 2 more sets over the weekend, a drum and bass B2B SABRE of @ivylab at @the_amp_smf stage and a cozy set at the Rabbit Hole with @mood_change_ . Will recap them in the many more posts to come! 

Thanks @colinmct for your candid captures, I love your style.

A highlight of @shambhala_mf was playing a very last minute b2b set with the Sabre of @ivylab & @themedicmc .  When @mrgoldie was unable to make it, @the_amp_smf asked if we would be interested in playing a dnb set later that night in his place. This was the first time we’d all played together and the set was so much fun!  1.5 hours flew by and I wish we could have kept going.  It ended up feeling so natural and was a nice extension to my friendship with Gove and an incredible way to get to know Medic.  Thank you @ims2gram 🤍

Thanks @dakredphotography & @bananacamphoto for freezing time with your images.

❄️THE LIBRARIAN❄️

Andrea Graham, better known by her stage name @librarianmusic, is a celebrated DJ, producer, and curator. She is the co-founder and music director of @basscoastfest – and is widely considered one of bass music’s leading creative minds and tastemakers. Equally an artist and entrepreneur, Andrea’s reputation as an inclusive community-builder in the electronic world has brought her a legion of fans and industry followers across the globe. 
As a DJ, The Librarian’s sets move through many genres of bass music – from UK Bass, footwork and jungle to 130, 140, UKG, and drum and bass – tying those diverse genres together with powerful low end frequencies and a deep connection with the dance floor.

We look forward to hosting Andrea Friday night on the @umbralsoundsystem stage!

We have a new home on wheels for the next few weeks and are slowly making our way up the coast from Sydney to Noosa. It’s amazing how many wide open and empty beaches line the coast. ☀️ We’ve found a good balance each day between work, surf, and enjoying really amazing coffee in every town. w/ @mood_change_ ❤️
